  "doc_id": "51446",
  "text": "In developing a banking Trojans defence taxonomy, we consider three dimensions, namely: detection, prevention and remedial actions [CITATION_1] . The first level of our taxonomy comprises different types of defences, and the second level is constructed based on how a specific defence type can be applied. Detection techniques can run at the host or at the network [CITATION_2] , while prevention techniques are classified as host-based, network-based and user training. Finally, remedial actions are divided into defensive and offensive activities; each linked to different techniques [CITATION_3] . ",
